text: Bunk club sandwich one day only aka they have extra turkey

Brian and I are drinking a 2008 Merlot from Five Star cellars in Walla Walla. It's awesome. Great year for vineyards in the Columbia valley, oldest dusty bottle in our rack. We tasted it at the winery when it was newly released, sharply tannic. Bought it. It was worth the wait. The years have mellowed it out to smoothness without collapsing: tart currant, leather, cherry, crushed flowers and warm volcanic rock. Yum. That is the story of our wine tonight.
